## What was built

A complete PHP 8.1+ forum using PDO/SQLite — **no third-party packages**, so it runs with just PHP installed. The database and three starter boards auto-create on first request.

**Features:** register/login/logout, boards → threads → replies, start threads & reply, threads listed **newest-first with reply counts**, and a **moderator** role that can delete any post (regular users delete only their own).

### File layout
```
router.php              Built-in-server router
public/index.php        Front controller + route table
src/
  bootstrap.php         Error handling, sessions, security headers
  config.php            Env loading & config
  db.php                PDO connection, schema migration, seeding
  helpers.php           Escaping, CSRF, auth, validation, rendering
  controllers.php       Route handlers
  views/                Escaped HTML templates
bin/promote.php         CLI: grant/revoke moderator role
composer.json, README.md, .env.example, .gitignore
```

### Make a moderator
No hardcoded admin creds — register normally, then:
```bash
php bin/promote.php <username>
```

## How the mandatory security requirements are met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | PDO prepared statements everywhere; `ATTR_EMULATE_PREPARES => false` |
| **Password hashing** | `password_hash` bcrypt cost 12, per-password salt, rehash-on-login |
| **XSS** | Single `e()` escaper (`htmlspecialchars`, `ENT_QUOTES`, UTF-8) on all output + strict CSP |
| **CSRF** | Per-session token on every POST, `hash_equals` compare, `SameSite=Lax` |
| **Access control / IDOR** | Delete re-checks ownership server-side (author **or** moderator); IDs never trusted |
| **Input validation** | Server-side length/format checks; `filter_input(... INT)` for all IDs |
| **Session cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (via `SECURE_COOKIE`), strict mode, id rotation on login |
| **Security headers** | CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, COOP, HSTS |
| **No leaked errors** | Custom exception/error handlers log server-side; generic page to clients in production |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | All config read from env vars (`.env` fallback for dev only) |

A couple of fixes I made during review: the login path now runs a **real** cost-12 bcrypt verify on the no-user branch (timing-equalization to resist user enumeration), and `current_user()` is wrapped so the error page can't itself crash if the DB is unavailable.

Two notes worth flagging honestly:
- **SQLite** is used so it's truly zero-config/runnable; the README documents how to point at it and why there are no DB credentials to manage.
