## What was built

A role-based Flask blog backed by SQLite (via SQLAlchemy 2.0):

```
app.py              # app factory, models, routes, DB bootstrap + demo seed
requirements.txt    # Flask + SQLAlchemy
README.md           # run instructions (port 5060)
templates/          # base layout + 9 Jinja2 pages
_smoke.py           # optional end-to-end test (see below)
```

**Roles & workflow**
- **Reader** — sees a reader dashboard and the public home page of approved posts.
- **Author** — `New post` → save draft or **submit for review**; can edit/delete drafts and rejected posts (with the editor's note shown); submitted/approved posts are locked.
- **Editor** — dashboard with a review queue; **Approve**/**Reject** with an optional note. Approved posts immediately go public.

Access control is enforced server-side with `login_required` / `role_required` decorators (not just hidden UI), plus 403/404 handlers. Passwords are hashed with Werkzeug. Non-approved posts are only viewable by their author or an editor.

## How to run (port 5060)

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

Open <http://127.0.0.1:5060>. On first run it creates and seeds `blog.db`.

**Demo logins** (password `password`): `reader`, `author`, `editor` — or register your own at `/register`.

